================================================================================
GAME CLASS
================================================================================

DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The Game class is the superclass for the entire system. It contains all shared
fields and behaviors required by every type of game. All fields are private to
enforce encapsulation.

FIELDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
id          -> unique identifier for each game
title       -> name of the game
genre       -> game category (Genre enum)
platform    -> platform the game runs on (Platform enum)
ageRating   -> age restriction (AgeRating enum)
rating      -> user rating (0–10)

CONSTRUCTOR
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
public Game(int id, String title, Genre genre, AgeRating ageRating, PlatForm platform) {
    this.id = id;
    this.title = title;
    this.genre = genre;
    this.platform = platform;
    this.ageRating = ageRating;
    this.rating = 0;
}

METHODS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
getTitle()
getGenre()
getPlatform()
getAgeRating()
getRating()
rateGame(int value)

toString()
    -> prints all game details in a readable format

================================================================================
GAME LIBRARY CLASS
================================================================================

DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GameLibrary acts as the system's database. All games are created, stored, and
managed here using a HashMap.

FIELDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
games  -> HashMap<Integer, Game>
nextId -> automatically assigns unique IDs

CONSTRUCTOR
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
public GameLibrary() {
    games = new HashMap<>();
    nextId = 1;
}

METHODS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
addGame(title, genre, ageRating, platform)
list()
listByGenre(genre)
listByPlatform(platform)
listByRating(rating)
search(text)
printLibraryDetails()

================================================================================
GAME SESSION CLASS
================================================================================

DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
GameSession records and stores information about gameplay sessions.

FIELDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
game      -> the game being played
duration  -> how long the session lasted

CONSTRUCTOR
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
public GameSession(Game game, int duration) {
    this.game = game;
    this.duration = duration;
}

METHODS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
startSession()
toString()

================================================================================
RATING LIBRARY CLASS
================================================================================

DESCRIPTION
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RatingLibrary stores ratings, comments, and written feedback for each game.

FIELDS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ratings   -> HashMap<Game, Integer>
comments  -> HashMap<Game, ArrayList<String>>

CONSTRUCTOR
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
public RatingLibrary() {
    ratings = new HashMap<>();
    comments = new HashMap<>();
}

METHODS
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------
rateGame(Game game, int rating)
addComments(Game game, String comment)
printWritings(Game game)

================================================================================
ENUMERATION TYPES
================================================================================

Platform   -> PC, PS5, XBOX, etc.
Genre      -> ACTION, RPG, SPORTS, etc.
AgeRating  -> KIDS, TEEN, ADULT

